cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with exhaustiveness checking of pattern-matching, which is a feature of functional programming languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses undecidability, which is a topic in logic and computability theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions type inference, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper deals with functional programming, which is a subfield of cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper discusses algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
